nd my mother said 'You're not having corsets you're having what you've got on, old fashioned stays we called them, they were made of a light flannel and mine were red on the inside and green on the out. And quilted, stitched, quilted in a diamond shaped p
a
ttern and a white button here and a white button on the back, no it wasn't a white button, the strap was fastened at the back, but you'd a white button here that would either drop it or lift it. And I - said 'Oh I'm the only one in the class that hasn't g
o
t corsets, she said it doesn't matter to me what the other girls have got you are having what you've got. She said 'You're not old enough for corsets and you're not having corsets so of course I couldn't have corsets, but I was nearly in tears when went i
n
