s
, that I can't supply to the others and I know I can't do it for the others, in fact I can't do it for one, you see she said and Mr Pardoe said - If you can manage to see your way to letting her go, I'll provide her with all that she needs wasn't that goo
d
 of him. But I couldn't go. I wanted to go to work. And I've just missed something, it must have been in the April of 1913 I think that the King and Queen came, or the March, and all the children went into Hanley Park and sang for them and they were all g
